<div id="review_3039343252" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3039343252" />
    <a title="Roksolana Mashkova" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23576371-roksolana-mashkova"><img alt="Roksolana Mashkova" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1567345241p2/23576371.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3039343252?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roksolana Mashkova" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roksolana Mashkova" href="/user/show/23576371-roksolana-mashkova">Roksolana Mashkova</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/33358517-the-death-and-life-of-great-american-cities">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3039343252" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6680559258358930576">It’s a great book which taught me to see what works well and what doesn’t in the city where I live (Tel Aviv). It showed me why so many of my favorite parts of the city work so perfectly. It also taught me to keep my phone in my bag and look around and analyze the city, as an entertaining and educational way to move around. I have to mention especially the light but articulate, humorous but precise language it’s written in. It’s accessible and the theory put forward here is very clear. Although </span>
  <span id="freeText6680559258358930576" style="display:none">It’s a great book which taught me to see what works well and what doesn’t in the city where I live (Tel Aviv). It showed me why so many of my favorite parts of the city work so perfectly. It also taught me to keep my phone in my bag and look around and analyze the city, as an entertaining and educational way to move around. I have to mention especially the light but articulate, humorous but precise language it’s written in. It’s accessible and the theory put forward here is very clear. Although it was written in the 1960s, it unfortunately feels very contemporary, because cities haven’t gotten rid of most (or arguably all) of the problems discussed by Jane Jacobs.</span>
